Wally Weitz's portfolios recovered some from the loss in 2008. He wrote: “Going forward, our working assumption is that the economy, and business values, will gradually bottom and recover slowly and unevenly. Eventually, a new bull market will begin.” Interestingly, he bought into educational companies. This is his Q2 portfolio update.Wallace Weitz buys Apollo Group Inc., Strayer Education Inc., sells Avon Products Inc., Bed Bath & Beyond Inc., DR PEPPER SNAPPLE GP, HSN, INC., Legg Mason Inc., Level 3 Communications Inc., TREE.COM, INC., UNITED STATES OIL FUND, LP during the 3-months ended 06/30/2009, according to the most recent filings of his investment company, Weitz Wallace R & Co. Wallace Weitz owns 58 stocks with a total value of $1.5 billion. These are the details of the buys and sells.New Purchases: APOL, STRA, Added Positions: ACIW, COP, CSTR, DEO, DVN, EXBD, KNOT, LBTYK, LINTA, PG, POT, XTO, INS, Reduced Positions: CAB, LMDIA, LOW, MHK, NCT, USG, WLP, Sold Out: AVP, BBBY, DPS, HSNI, LM, LVLT, TREE, USO, For the details of Wallace Weitz's stock buys and sells, go to the Link HereThis is the sector weightings of Wallace Weitz's portfolio:These are the top 5 holdings of Wallace WeitzBerkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK-B) - 57,607 shares, 10.85% of the total portfolioRedwood Trust Inc. (RWT) - 6,270,955 shares, 6.02% of the total portfolioWellPoint Inc. (WLP) - 1,627,130 shares, 5.38% of the total portfolioTEL AND DATA SYS (TDS-S) - 2,693,105 shares, 4.55% of the total portfolioDell Inc. (DELL) - 5,016,679 shares, 4.48% of the total portfolioAdded: The Procter & Gamble Company (NYSE:PG)Wallace Weitz added to his holdings in The Procter & Gamble Company by 250%. His purchase prices were between $48.38 and $52.76, with an estimated average price of $50.8. The impact to his portfolio due to this purchase was 0.41%. His holdings were 175,000 shares as of 06/30/2009. The Procter & Gamble Company manufactures and markets a broad range of consumer products in many countries