Our People
  


A A A










Our People




The people who make up our firm are the core of who we are, and the reason we can do what we do so well. Many have been with us for more than a decade, and they know how to give our shareholders what they need. Meet the team who’s responsible for introducing investors to the Weitz Way.









              Wallace Weitz, CFA
              Co-Chief Investment Officer, Portfolio Manager


As founder
and co-chief investment officer of Weitz Investments, Wally has spent over
three decades putting his instinct for opportunity to work for shareholders.
Influenced by the value investing model of Benjamin Graham and Warren Buffett,
Wally has steadily produced outstanding results on the funds that he’s managed.
He manages Partners III Opportunity Fund and co-manages Partners Value Fund and
Hickory Fund.

Wally discovered Benjamin Graham’s concept of value investing in high school.
Already an investor (he made his first stock buy at the age of 12), he
recognized a common-sense approach when he saw it. After earning a BA in
economics at Carleton College in 1970, Wally spent three years in New York
doing security analysis before coming to Omaha and joining Chiles, Heider &
Co. in 1973. There, he spent 10 years as an analyst and portfolio manager until
he started Wallace R. Weitz & Company in 1983. 

Wally has made a career out of his favorite hobby, investing. When he’s not
doing that, he loves to golf, travel, read and work with charitable and
educational foundations. Wally is on the Board of Trustees for Carleton College
and serves on various other non-profit boards.







              Ken Stoll
              President


As far as Ken is concerned, his sole focus at Weitz Investments is to help clients achieve their goals. And when he sees everyone on staff working together to make that happen, it’s a very satisfying experience for him. 

Ken came to the company in 2004 as chief financial officer and became president at the end of 2014. Before that, he spent more than 20 years working as a certified public accountant in the investment management industry. Ken had the honor of serving on the AICPA Investment Companies Committee for two years, contributing to a major update to the organization’s Audit and Accounting Guide for Investment Companies. He holds a bachelor’s degree from Saint John’s University.


Ken spends his free time golfing and coaching a high school lacrosse team.







              Bradley P. Hinton, CFA
              Co-Chief Investment Officer, Portfolio Manager


Brad may be co-chief investment officer, but
he’s the type of leader who values collaboration. His focus is encouraging the
investment team to work together to make a meaningful difference in our
clients’ lives.

Brad joined the company in 2001 as a research analyst and was appointed co-CIO
in April 2017. His experience in equity analysis, fixed income credit research
and portfolio management enables him to see opportunities from multiple angles.
He became sole manager of the Balanced Fund in August 2005 and also co-manages
Value Fund and Partners Value Fund. Brad holds a bachelor’s degree from the
University of Nebraska and a master’s from Dartmouth, but he never stops
learning. Brad enjoys the intellectual stimulation of working with other
talented, passionate colleagues at Weitz Investments. 

Brad serves the community by volunteering for youth baseball and other sports.
The parents of three great kids, Brad and his wife Christie are also big
College World Series fans. Their attendance streak of at least one game per
season is at 23 years and counting.







              Andrew S. Weitz
              Director of Equity Research, Portfolio Manager


A naturally curious person, in his role as
director of equity research, Drew thrives in learning about many different
businesses, how they fit into a very dynamic world and into our equity
portfolios. 

Drew first came to Weitz Investment Management, Inc. in 1998, while a student
at Carleton College, working in various departments including client services,
operations and research. After graduating in 2002 with a bachelor’s degree in
computer science, he moved to Chicago in 2004 where he worked as a research
associate and research analyst for Ariel Investments. In 2008, Drew returned to
Omaha and Weitz Investments as an equity research analyst. He became co-manager
of Hickory Fund in December 2011 and was appointed director of equity research
in April 2017.

Drew volunteers on the advisors group for
OneWorld Community Health Centers and serves on the boards of The UNION for
Contemporary Art and Carleton College’s Alumni Annual Fund. On his own time, he
golfs, plays guitar and runs, but his favorite hobby is whatever his kids are
interested in.







              Nolan P. Anderson
              Research Analyst, Portfolio Manager


As one of our research analysts, Nolan spends his days digging out all the relevant facts that tell us which companies are promising opportunities – and which ones aren’t. Nolan is also a co-portfolio manager of the Core Plus Income Fund and Ultra Short Government Fund.

Nolan joined the company in November 2011 and co-manages the Core Plus Income Fund and Ultra Short Government Fund. He has found that the friendly Weitz atmosphere makes his job more fun and enjoyable. Previously, he performed financial modeling and due diligence on leveraged buyout transactions for Wells Fargo Bank in San Francisco. From 2004-2007 he worked as a commercial real estate research analyst for Woodmen of the World Life Insurance Society in Omaha. He holds a bachelor’s degree in real estate and land use economics and a master’s in business administration from the University of Nebraska at Omaha.

Nolan is an avid reader, focusing on history, psychology and behavioral economics. He also plays golf, and once spent four months traveling through 16 countries in Europe, the Middle East and Southeast Asia.







              Jonathan A. Baker, CFA
              Research Analyst, Portfolio Manager


Jon thrives under the freedom that he has been given to pursue the right course of action for Weitz Investments shareholders. The Weitz Way of investing is just Jon’s natural way of doing business.

He has co-managed the Research Fund since its Inception and of the predecessor Research Partnership since April 2005. Before he became an equity analyst for Weitz Investments in 1997, Jon audited equity funds as a certified public accountant. He holds a bachelor’s degree in accounting and computer applications from the University of Notre Dame. Above all, he appreciates the “license to learn” that Weitz employees are granted.

Jon enjoys spending time with friends, traveling and golf.  







              Mary Bickels
              Client Service Manager


Mary exemplifies customer service in every way. Our client services department wouldn’t be the same without her. In fact, Wally Weitz himself has said this company couldn’t do what it does without her.

Mary has been part of Weitz Investments since 1993. She previously worked with Wally Weitz at a different brokerage firm for almost 10 years. She believes there’s no better place to work than where she is today.


Mary and her husband call themselves “professional fans” of most sports teams and they’re at various games rooting for their favorites whenever possible.








              Thomas D. Carney, CFA
              Portfolio Manager


Tom’s conservative instinct makes him a perfect candidate to manage our fixed income portfolios; whose first objective is preservation of capital. Tom is the portfolio manager of the Nebraska Tax-Free Income Fund and Short Duration Income Fund and co-manager of the Core Plus Income Fund and Ultra Short Government Fund.

Tom began his investment career in 1982 at Chiles, Heider & Co., Inc., a regional brokerage firm in Omaha, where he held several positions. In 1986, he became a municipal securities professional with Smith Barney in Omaha. Four years later, he completed his BS in finance at the University of Nebraska at Omaha. He joined Weitz Investments in 1995. Tom has been a CFA® charterholder since 1999 and was the president of the CFA Society of Nebraska from 2005-2006.







              Matt Case
              Client Services Representative


Matt appreciates working at a company where employees are both literally
and figuratively invested in its success. He believes problem solving is much
easier when working alongside a friend, and that is the experience he hopes to
provide each time he has contact with a client.

Before joining Weitz Investments in May 2015, Matt worked at Now
You Know Investigations as a marketing assistant/private investigator. Prior to
his time there, he worked at Vyral Marketing as a marketing coach and video
editor.

Matt earned a BA in organizational communication from Doane
College in Nebraska. He also holds Series 6 and 63 licenses.

In
his spare time, Matt volunteers at the local Joslyn Castle as one of the
“Joslyn Castle Players,” performing various roles in murder mystery dinner
theatre plays. He also loves reading, writing, history, geography and music (Matt
has played guitar for over 20 years). 







              John Detisch
              General Counsel and Chief Compliance Officer


As general counsel and chief compliance officer, John takes great pride in the fact that everyone at Weitz Investments is self-motivated to stay in compliance with all laws and regulations. 

John joined the company in January of 2011 after a respected career in law at Kutak Rock LLP. He earned his Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of Kansas and his law degree from Harvard Law School. 

When he’s not keeping the Weitz staff on their toes, John and his wife are busy raising almost 5-year-old twins and an 8-year-old. 







              John Gabriel, CFP®
              East Regional Director


As a regional director, John is constantly helping advisers work for positive investor outcomes, a focus that is supported throughout Weitz Investments.

John became part of the team in 2011 after working  in the mutual fund industry for 14 years. He has an MBA from the University of Colorado with concentrations in entrepreneurship and corporate finance and an undergraduate degree from the University of Denver. While working at Rydex Funds, he  won several awards from that company, including two for assets under management growth and one for new client development. But finance wasn’t always John’s focus. He started out as a sixth-grade teacher.

John loves basketball, playing on a recreational league and coaching teams for his four children. He also enjoys skiing, hiking, woodworking and going to concerts. Education is in his blood, and he continues to take classes to improve his professional skills. He recently passed his CFP exam and is in the process of sitting for the CIMA. 







              Martha Gilchrist
              Vice President, Director of Operations


Martha joined Weitz Investments in 1993 and serves as our
director of operations. Prior to joining our firm, she was employed at Shearson
Lehman Brothers (formerly EF Hutton and Shearson Lehman Hutton), where she
worked in operations, primarily running the wire desk. Martha earned a BS in accounting
from Minnesota State University-Moorhead.







              Rachelle Hill
              Client Services Representative


Rachelle takes a lot of pride in her work and in her affiliation with Weitz Investments. She believes the thoughtful, family-friendly culture is a great environment, and it shows in the service she provides to our clients.


Before joining Weitz in 2000, Rachelle worked at Blue Cross and Blue Shield of Nebraska in the membership and claims-processing departments. She has a bachelor’s degree in English from the University of South Dakota.

At home, Rachelle and her husband enjoy the comedy stylings of their son. Rachelle also makes time for reading and writing.








              Barton B. Hooper, CFA
              Research Analyst, Portfolio Manager


Barton arrived at Weitz Investments in 2007 with a passion for investing, intellectual honesty and critical thinking. His work as a research analyst gives him the opportunity to explore different companies and industries on a daily basis.

When it comes to investing, Barton’s philosophy is marked by a penchant for challenging the status quo, a characteristic that makes him a perfect fit for the Weitz Way of investing. He currently co-manages the Research Fund and has since 2008. His background includes working as a research analyst at Oak Value Capital Management (Durham, N.C.) and Trilogy Capital Management (Kansas City, Mo.). He also spent several years as a mergers and acquisitions investment banker and CPA after graduating from the University of Missouri with a bachelor’s degree in accounting, and Washington University with a master’s degree in finance.

A family man, Barton spends his weekends at his children's activities. He enjoys studying history and philosophy in his spare time.







              Kevin Joy
              Regional Director


In his role as regional director, Kevin identifies, develops and cultivates
strategic relationships with institutional investors and financial
intermediaries. Prior to joining Weitz Investments in 2015, Kevin spent five
years at Heartland Advisors in the role of vice president of institutional sales
and marketing. Prior to his time there, Kevin was with New York Life Insurance
Company/NYLEX Benefits as managing director, Midwest. From 1998 to 2009, Kevin served
as vice president and regional director in the Investment Management and
Private Wealth Management Divisions at Goldman Sachs.

Kevin earned a BS in mechanical and biomedical engineering from
Carnegie Mellon University and an MBA in finance Washington University in Saint
Louis. He holds Series 7 and 65 licenses and earned the Claritas® Investment
Certificate. In 2012, Kevin was included in DiversityMBA
Magazine’s Top 100 Under 50 Diverse Executive & Emerging Leaders. Prior
to his roles in financial services, Kevin was an advisory client manager at
IBM, where he was the recipient of several IBM Marketing Excellence Awards.

In his spare time, Kevin serves as a board member for both City
Year Milwaukee and the Rogers Memorial Hospital Foundation. He is also an emeritus
member of the Auxiliary Board of the Art Institute of Chicago.







              Kelly Kraft, CIMA®
              Director of National Accounts


The culture and people of Weitz Investments make Kelly feel as though she is working with family.

Before joining us as Director of National Accounts in 2015, Kelly spent more than 18 years as a strategic account manager at Lord Abbett. Prior to that, she was a regional manager for Nuveen Investments, Eastern division.  Kelly’s experience fits well into our investment-led, collaborative environment. She feels that the open communication, team approach and encouraging management style is truly unique in our industry. 

Kelly earned her bachelor’s degree in political science from Illinois State University. She is a member of IMCA and BISA and holds the CIMA® designation. In her free time, Kelly enjoys traveling, boating and golf.







              David Kratz
              Product Specialist


Most of the time, you’ll find David introducing Weitz Investments to registered investment advisers across the nation.

David started at Weitz in client services, working with direct shareholders after he graduated from Creighton with his bachelor’s degree in finance in 2004. Five years later, he interned on the equity side of the business. He’s gone on to earn two master’s degrees – one in business administration and a second in security analysis and portfolio management – and he’s currently toying with the idea of returning one more time for a Ph.D.

When David’s away from the office, you’ll find him with his family and friends, preferably outdoors. He spends his vacations in Colorado or Montana, either fishing or skiing depending on weather. David is also working on his rock-climbing skills.







              Ann Krone
              Client Services Representative


Ann’s role as client service representative puts her in front of Weitz Investments clients on a daily basis. Since she joined the company in 1998, her love of working with people has enabled her to make sure that all our clients get the service they deserve.

Ann received a bachelor’s degree in business administration from Iowa State University, later earning her master’s from Drake University in Des Moines. Before bringing her customer service skills to Weitz Investments, she served as a bank examiner for the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC), a cost analyst for telecommunications giant Sprint, and a project manager for Mutual of Omaha.

Outside of the office, Ann stays busy attending her triplet's college activities. She also enjoys reading and cooking.







              Lori M. Kuhlmann
              Trader


Lori juggles a number of research support tasks in addition to her role trading securities for the Weitz Investments. She enjoys working with portfolio managers, analysts and contra-side traders daily to ensure effective execution of security transactions for investors. 

Lori has been with Weitz Investments since 1999, and she still finds it easy to come to work every day because of the professional, intelligent working environment. After earning her Bachelor of Arts degree from Midland Lutheran College, she worked for various companies in the financial services industry.

Outside of work, Lori prefers spending time with family and friends.







              Gina Ladd
              Content and Communications Specialist


Gina was drawn to the Firm by its forward-thinking approach. The friendly, positive and team-first attitude of the professionals at Weitz Investments provides the perfect surroundings for her to help shape our marketing strategy. 

She comes to us with several years of experience as Manager of Product Marketing at Mutual of Omaha and prior to that was a Public and Community Relations Coordinator for Harrah’s and Bluffs Run Casinos.

Gina has her MBA from Bellevue University and a BA in Journalism and Mass Communications from Creighton University. In her free time, she enjoys running, playing volleyball and spending time with her daughter and husband. Gina is also a certified group cycling instructor.







              Sean Mihal
              West Regional Director


Sean finds great satisfaction in having the freedom to express and implement ideas for the benefit of investors. His focus is providing value to advisors through both financial return and customer service.


Before joining Weitz Investments, Sean shaped his career at several large investing corporations. He started his financial career as an advisor for Morgan Stanley Dean Witter in 1998, then moved to a similar role with Charles Schwab.  In 2003 Sean joined the advisor services group at Schwab, where he worked as Business Development Officer consulting advisors on the advantages of building independently owned and operated RIA’s.  Over his 8+ year career recruiting advisors to Schwab Sean earned several sales awards . Sean holds a Bachelor of Science degree from Loyola University in Chicago. 

Sean and his wife have two young girls. While his calendar is now filling up with fatherly pursuits in soccer, ballet and music, he still makes time to run, ski and surf. Sean also volunteers with the Heal the Bay Foundation, a program dedicated to improving the quality of beaches and neighborhoods surrounding Santa Monica Bay in California.








              Yana Morgan, CFP®
              Midwest Regional Director


For Yana, it’s a pleasure to work with local and national clients every day. She enjoys having the chance to speak with different people, each with a different personality and different stories to tell.


Yana’s enthusiasm for Weitz Investments stems from feeling good about what she does and the services she provides. Before joining the company in 2000 as a client services representative, Yana was director of donor services for the Omaha Community Foundation. She also has a background in politics, having served as a legislative assistant for U.S. Sen. Chuck Hagel and managed several Nebraska campaigns. Yana has a bachelor’s in psychology from Southern Connecticut State University.


When she is not serving our clients, Yana serves as a
board member for both Girl’s Incorporated of Omaha and Financial Planning
Association of Nebraska. She loves jazz, reading, cooking and numerous activities to stay in shape.








              Jessica Nagengast, CFP®
              Associate Director


In her Internal Sales Associate role, Jessica not only provides superior support to the sales team, she also reaches out to advisers across the country introducing the Weitz Way. 

Before joining Weitz in 2013, Jessica worked at Carson Wealth Management Group as an Associate Wealth Advisor and Wealth Plan Design Coordinator. She graduated from Marquette University, majoring in Finance and Marketing.

In her spare time, Jessica enjoys cycling, archery and trap shooting and currently serves on the board of Nebraska Friends of Foster Children.







              David A. Perkins, CFA
              Research Analyst, Portfolio Manager


There’s nothing Dave likes better than a challenge. In his role, he gets plenty of them at Weitz Investments. He has been portfolio co-manager for the Weitz Value Fund since December 2011. 

Dave enjoys the ongoing challenge of finding new investment opportunities for our clients, and he thrives amid the camaraderie of the Weitz Investments team. Before joining the company in 2004, Dave honed his analytical skills at McCarthy Group Asset Management. He has a Bachelor of Science degree in business systems from Taylor University in Upland, Ind. 

Dave and his wife, Courtney, have three children. He enjoys running, playing recreational basketball and traveling. Dave also makes time for reading and stays involved with his church. 







              Nathan F. Ritz, CFA
              Research Analyst, Portfolio Manager


Nathan wouldn’t necessarily call himself a devil’s advocate, but he certainly appreciates the way independent thinking is valued at Weitz Investments. It’s a great way to identify unique opportunities for our clients.

He has been a co-manager of the Research Fund since December 2016. Nathan was immediately drawn to the company’s collaborative and friendly working environment and joined the team in 2011. Before that, he worked as an analyst for West Gate Bank. He completed an internship with Moody Aldrich Partners in Boston after finishing his bachelor’s degree in finance, economics and mathematics from the University of Nebraska-Lincoln. He became a CFA® charterholder in 2015.

Volunteering for nonprofits is a priority for Nathan. He previously served on the board of Rebuilding Together-Lincoln. He also enjoys reading and running marathons.







              Debbie Stalnaker
              Trading/Portfolio Assistant


Debbie's work experience gets put to good use in her role supporting our separate accounts and assisting our trading desk and research team.

Debbie came to Weitz in 2014 from Westwood Holdings Group (previously McCarthy Group Advisors) where she was a Portfolio Administrator. Prior to
Westwood, she worked at AllianceBernstein in Chicago where her role grew from Portfolio Assistant to Associate PM/Assistant VP. Her BA is in business administration from Loyola University Chicago.


Debbie spends most of her free time chasing her 2 toddlers - around the park, pool or really anywhere outside. She loves to travel and ski, when free time permits!







              Grant Tesnohlidek
              Associate Director


Grant joined Weitz
Investments in December 2015. In his role, Grant not only provides support to
our regional directors but also has the opportunity to develop and cultivate
meaningful relationships with advisors across the country. 

Before joining Weitz,
Grant was an Internal Sales and Recruiting Consultant with Mutual of Omaha, where
he traveled around the country assisting division office management with their
sales strategy and recruiting efforts. Prior to his time there, Grant spent six
years at TD Ameritrade as a New Client Development Consultant, assisting new
and prospective retail clients with everything from industry questions to
investment strategy and asset allocation concerns. During his time at TD
Ameritrade, Grant was consistently a President’s Club Award recipient for his
ability to gather additional client assets. He was also a four-time recipient
of the Customer Service Index Award, with a perfect client satisfaction rating.

Grant has a BA in
Psychology from Creighton University. He also holds Series 7 and 66 licenses. 

Outside of work, Grant’s interests include chasing his very active
three-year-old son, playing hockey and running. He also enjoys surfing and
snowboarding (when he can get to an ocean or mountain). 







              Dan Walker, CFA
              Research Analyst, Portfolio Manager


Dan Walker joined Weitz Investment Management, Inc. in July 2015. He has been a co-manager of the Research Fund since December 2016. Prior to joining the Firm, Dan spent four years as a Research Analyst for Heartland Advisors in Milwaukee, WI. Before his time in the investment management field, Dan worked as a Copy Chief for Bozell in Omaha, NE for nine years focusing on brand strategy and creative execution for companies in various sectors including healthcare and financial services. He was also an Account Manager for Research Systems Corporation in Evansville, IN. Dan graduated from the University of Evansville with a BFA in Creative Writing and received an MBA in Applied Security Analysis from the University of Wisconsin-Madison. Dan is a CFA® charterholder.




